   English Language Help for International Students
</h1>
<p class="style1"><img src="Images/indianstudent.jpg" alt="International Student" width="300" height="200" hspace="2" border="1" align="right" />Abertay is an exciting place to be. We put our students first and work hard to ensure you receive the guidance, support and help you need to get the most of your studies and wider University life. You may want to think about additional support prior to commencing your studies if your first language is not English. You can enrol on either the summer Pre-Sessional Programme or the full time English Language preparation programme. Both of these programmes will help, aid and assist you with your studies and ensure you make the most of your study time at Abertay. You will also find on these pages the English language requirements accepted by the University.</p>
<p class="style1"><a href="EnglishPreSessional.cfm?Key=003.004.010.002">Pre-Sessional Programme for International Students</a> - A summer programme for international students who wish to improve their English or work on their study skills.</p>

<p class="style1"><a href="EnglishPreparation.cfm?Key=003.004.010.003">English Language Preparation Programme</a></b> - A full-time course running from September to May. It is designed for students with a good educational background who need to develop their English language skills and academic study skills in English before they begin their degree courses.</p>
<p class="style1"><a href="EnglishStudy.cfm?Key=003.004.010.004">English for Study</a></b> - While you are studying on your degree course, you can take free English support classes throughout your first year at Abertay.</p>
